    "about": "Appear ASA is a Norwegian live production technology company founded in 2004 by Thomas Lind and headquartered in Oslo. The company designs and delivers high-capacity, sustainable solutions for media processing and live content delivery to Tier-1 broadcasters, production companies, content owners, and network operators worldwide. Its technology enables the capture, transport, and processing of live video from sports stadiums and concert arenas with ultra-low latency. Key customers include NBCUniversal, Warner Bros. Discovery, Fox Sports, Formula 1, Sky, BT, and Eurovision. Appear listed on Euronext Oslo Børs in November 2025 after an oversubscribed IPO. CEO is Thomas Bostrøm Jørgensen. Full-year 2025 revenue guidance was NOK 800M, representing 35% CAGR from 2021.",
